Reasoning: The paper deals with the impact of imperfect channel state information, residual additive transceiver hardware impairments, and channel aging on the performance of multiple-antenna base stations in heterogeneous cellular networks. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT), networked systems (cs.NI), communication systems (cs.COMM), and possibly multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and control systems (cs.SY).
